JOHANNESBURG – The Premier Soccer League Disciplinary Committee on Tuesday found both Black Leopards FC and Jomo Cosmos FC guilty on charges of misconduct. Black Leopards FC were charged with failure to provide adequate security during the National First Division play-off match against Jomo Cosmos FC. They were fined R150, 000 - suspended for 24 months. They were also ordered to pay costs of the sitting amounting to R33,000. READ: Premier Soccer League to appeal high court ruling In a second matter, Jomo Cosmos FC were also found guilty of contravening the Sport and Recreational Events Safety Act after it allowed supporters to enter the stadium without tickets during their Promotion Play-off match against Black Leopards FC on May 20. Jomo Cosmos FC have been fined R125 000 - suspended for 24 months. African News Agency